  "title": "2.5D Puzzle Game — P1 Games",
  "desc": "A 2.5D puzzle game I built at P1 Game Company featuring <span class=\"syn-str\">player movement systems</span>, <span class=\"syn-str\">object fading mechanics</span> and <span class=\"syn-str\">dual character switching</span>.",
  "aim": "Implement core gameplay systems for a 2.5D puzzle game in a professional studio environment, focusing on smooth player mechanics and interactive puzzle elements.",
  "about": "Developed as part of a team project at P1 Game Company where I worked as a programmer. My main responsibilities included implementing player movement systems and programming puzzle mechanics such as making walls turn invisible to aid navigation when solving challenges.\n\nThe project involved three core systems — a Rigidbody-based movement controller that rotates the player sprite to face the direction of movement, an ObjectFader that smoothly interpolates material opacity to reveal or hide puzzle elements, and a PlayerSwitch system that seamlessly transfers control between two characters while updating the camera and UI dynamically.",
  "takeaways": "Working at a real game company was a completely different experience from university projects. Deadlines were real, standards were higher, and every system had to integrate cleanly with other people's work. I learned how to write code that other developers can actually use — clean, well structured and predictable. The ObjectFader in particular taught me how much polish matters — a smooth fade feels completely different from an instant toggle.",
  "thanks": "Thanks to the team at P1 Game Company — designers, animators and fellow programmers — for a genuinely collaborative and professional development experience.",
