  "title": "2D Shooter Game",
  "desc": "A 2D shooter I built at P1 Games where players pilot a rocket through waves of enemies, collecting fuel and power-ups while <span class=\"syn-str\">upgrading speed, health and fuel capacity</span>.",
  "aim": "Implement enemy AI systems, procedural spawning and UI menus for a 2D shooter game in a team environment.",
  "about": "Developed as part of a team project at P1 Game Company where I worked as the lead programmer (P1). Players pilot a rocket through waves of enemies, surviving as long as possible while collecting fuel and power-ups and unlocking upgrades for speed, health and fuel capacity.\n\nMy responsibilities covered two main areas — enemy systems and UI. For enemies I implemented distinct behaviour patterns for each enemy type: the StormCloud moves back and forth flipping direction when reaching a set distance, the HotAirBalloon takes damage from bullets and randomly spawns fuel or gold pickups on death, and the Airplane spawner procedurally instantiates enemies at random locations on a timed interval. I also built the full menu system including upgrade selection, pause screen and HUD elements.",
  "takeaways": "This project taught me how to design enemy systems that feel varied and fair without being overwhelming. Each enemy needed its own personality — movement pattern, reward, threat level — and balancing all of that required constant playtesting and iteration. I also got much more comfortable with Unity's collision system and learned how procedural spawning can dramatically change the feel of a game without adding much code complexity.",
  "thanks": "Thanks to the full team at P1 Game Company for the collaboration — particularly the designers who helped balance the upgrade system and the artists who brought the enemies to life.",
